com.arjuna.mw.wscf.model.as.coordinator
Interface Coordinator

public interface Coordinator

The generic coordinator interface. All coordinator implementations must at least conform to this interface.

Since:
1.0.
Version:
$Id: Coordinator.java,v 1.1 2003/01/07 10:33:41 nmcl Exp $
Author:
Mark Little (mark.little@arjuna.com)

coordinate

public Outcome coordinate(CompletionStatus cs)
                   throws WrongStateException,
                          ProtocolViolationException,
                          SystemException
Coordinate the participants using the completion status provided.
Parameters:
CompletionStatus - cs The CompletionStatus to use.
Returns:
the result of completing the activity. Null is valid and must be interpreted within the context of any HLS that may exist.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the current activity is not in a state that allows it to be coordinated, or is incompatible with the completion status provided.
ProtocolViolationException - Thrown if the a violation of the activity service or HLS protocol occurs.
SystemException - Thrown if some other error occurred.
See Also:
Outcome

addParticipant

public void addParticipant(Participant act,
                           int priority,
                           Qualifier[] quals)
                    throws WrongStateException,
                           DuplicateParticipantException,
                           InvalidParticipantException,
                           SystemException
Register the specified participant with the coordinator.
Parameters:
Participant - act The participant to enroll with the coordinator.
int - priority If the coordinator allows prioritisation of participants, this priority is used to ensure participant invocations occur in a specific order.
Qualifier[] - quals Any qualifiers associated with the participant for this registration.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the coordinator is not in a state that allows participants to be registered.
DuplicateParticipantException - Thrown if the participant has already been registered with this coordinator.
InvalidParticipantException - Thrown if the partcipant is invalid.
SystemException - Thrown if any other error occurs.

                       throws InvalidParticipantException,
                              WrongStateException,
                              SystemException
Unregister the specified participant from the coordinator.
Parameters:
Participant - act The participant to remove.
Throws:
InvalidParticipantException - Thrown if the partcipant is not known of by the coordinator.
WrongStateException - Thrown if the coordinator is not in a state that allows participants to be removed.
SystemException - Thrown if any other error occurs.

setResponse

public void setResponse(java.lang.String id,
                        Message notification,
                        Outcome response,
                        Qualifier[] quals)
                 throws InvalidParticipantException,
                        WrongStateException,
                        SystemException
Some coordination protocol will allow participants to make autonomous decisions based upon their current state and assumptions about which notifications a coordinator may send them.
Parameters:
String - id The unique participant name.
Message - notification The notification that the participant has based the response on. For example, the response is related to a "prepare" notification.
Outcome - response The response to the assumed notification.
Qualifier[] - quals Any qualifiers associated with the response.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the coordinator is not in a state that is compatible with the received response.
InvalidParticipantException - Thrown if the participant is not known to the coordinator.
SystemException - Thrown if any other error occurs.
